## Deployment (Vercel + GitHub)

**Pattern**: One GitHub repo (this monorepo), one Vercel project per client.

**Vercel project settings per client**:
- **Root Directory**: `apps/<slug>` (e.g. `apps/cipher-billing`)
- **Framework**: Next.js
- **Install**: pnpm install (at repo root)
- **Build**: `pnpm --filter @sweetmedia/<slug> build` (or turbo filter equivalent)

**Required environment variables per Vercel project**:
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` — `https://<ref>.supabase.co`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` — anon/public key
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` — same anon key (both set)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_ID` — slug (e.g. `cipher-billing`)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` — canonical URL (e.g. `https://cipherbilling.com`)
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` — for postbuild sync and admin API routes
- `RESEND_API_KEY` — contact form email delivery
- Optional: `CONTACT_BRAND_NAME`, `CONTACT_TO_EMAIL`, `CONTACT_FROM_EMAIL` (contact route)
- Optional: `TRACKED_PAGE_METADATA_CACHE_SECONDS`

**Scaffold auto-writes** `.env.local` with the first five vars when `setup-new-client.mjs` runs successfully. Mirror these to Vercel manually (or via Vercel API script — not yet built).

